    {
      "song": "Girls Camp",
      "era": "Current",
      "core_hook": "A song about loving someone in the present while memory keeps arriving with old names.",
      "anecdotes": [
        "A friend of a friend was once part of a girls-camp memory, then became he, and the old rule no longer had a place for him.",
        "The song is not arguing with who he is; it admits that memory can be slower than language.",
        "The pronoun chorus works like a practice drill: trying to say the right thing while the past catches up.",
        "Its bluesy roots feeling connects Lily's earlier sound to the newer Analog Myth lens."
