    {
      "song": "No Mortgage",
      "era": "Current",
      "core_hook": "No mortgage, no rent, no split: Lily makes the dream smaller until it stops lying.",
      "anecdotes": [
        "A tiny house and cheap land become a refusal of financial obligations, people obligations, and institutions with hands in her pockets.",
        "The song keeps the Wi-Fi on but turns the performance of availability off.",
        "Ramen runs and distance are not glamorized; they are the practical math of staying free.",
        "The spacious sound leaves room around the idea, like the song found cheap land and refused to overbuild."
      ],
