    {
      "song": "Spilling the Tea",
      "era": "Current",
      "core_hook": "Afternoon tea promises variety, but Lily hears the copy-paste loop under the polite tablecloth.",
      "anecdotes": [
        "Afternoon tea is sold as curated variety, but enough visits reveal the same menu loop.",
        "The cucumber sandwiches, salmon she does not like, and scones keep coming back under new names.",
        "Even the conversation starts to feel staged: polite, surface-level, and interchangeable.",
        "The electronic bass makes the ritual feel glossy, artificial, and slightly too pleased with itself.",
        "It is not gossip and not literal spilled tea; it is repetition with manners."
      ],
