    {
      "song": "Slow Walk",
      "era": "Current",
      "core_hook": "Slow Walk is pace as self-defense.",
      "anecdotes": [
        "Lily will get out in front and slow down so the group has to stop rushing.",
        "The song answers the time anxiety of Analog Myth with cool refusal instead of panic.",
        "It is not laziness; it is a tiny protest against treating speed like proof of worth.",
        "The gentle, melodic vocals keep lifting the song forward while the lyric refuses to hurry."
      ],
