    {
      "song": "Guards Down",
      "era": "Current",
      "core_hook": "Dropping the guards did not make it better. It made it real.",
      "anecdotes": [
        "Guards Down started with candlepin bowling with Da on a cruise ship.",
        "Lily pressed the guard-rail button the other way: guards down.",
        "She kept switching hands, with left feeling natural and right feeling possible.",
        "The exposed throw is the emotional center: no correction, no soft edges, just whatever happens."
      ],
