    {
      "song": "Analog Myth",
      "era": "Current",
      "core_hook": "If you cannot read clocks, maybe time is just a myth.",
      "anecdotes": [
        "The song starts with analog clocks at the front of the classroom and students quietly using Chromebooks instead.",
        "The Apple Watch kid becomes the accidental time authority: the truth strapped to someone's wrist.",
        "The title track turns one wall clock, one Chromebook, one Apple Watch, and a general sense of doom into anti-clock philosophy.",
        "The violin gives the song a darker haunted-clock edge."
      ],
